    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2–1152:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 189<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1952—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>885. Re section 5 <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1165.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d189fn1">
                        <ref target="#d184">Document 184</ref>.</note> Your statement to Subardjo
                    that he shld not mix Battle Act and <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> embargo
                    with <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> assurances correct. <gloss
                        target="#t_PNI1">PNI</gloss> entirely in error believing US wld construe
                    Part 3 of para 1 to mean <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> wld have to
                    contribute all exports US. Under Battle Act US expects <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> confine exports Title I items to free countries and if Title
                    II items exported outside such area then only in return real <hi rend="italic"
                        >quid pro quo</hi> and in limited quantities.</p>
                <p>Since <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> note of Jan 23 wld cause unfavorable
                    impression on US Cong if it were to be quoted as evidence that <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt not giving all assurances required under
                        <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_RI1">RI</gloss> shld not use note in debate. While US was
                    desirous receiving note indicating willingness <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> fully to cooperate in prohibiting export Title I items no
                    formal US reply is contemplated on adequacy <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> note even though note not clear as to control measures
                    applicable to Title I items. There is no question of terminating assistance
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> under Battle Act as long as <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> actions re Title I are believed to meet US
                    policy objectives as set forth in Act. US has no reason believe <pb facs="0286"
                        n="266" xml:id="pg_266"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> actions are not in accord with these
                    objectives re Title I. US has not yet developed specific proposals re Title
                    II.</p>
                <p>Dept hopes authorizations contained in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                        850<note n="2" xml:id="d189fn2">Reference should be to telegram 856 (see
                            <ref target="#d184fn2">footnote 2, Document 184</ref>); telegram 850,
                        not printed, deals with New Guinea.</note> will prove acceptable to <gloss
                        target="#t_RI1">RI</gloss>.</p>
                <p>In event that alternatives contained in <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>
                    are not adequate you shld keep open possibility further negot this point and
                    report to Dept any further counter proposals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
